-{"id":"franken_numpy-rosd","title":"Working-tree hygiene: triage 80+ untracked scratch files in repo root","description":"## Why this exists\n\ngit status at the repo root currently lists 80+ untracked files left by previous agent debugging sessions: test_*.rs, test_*.py, clippy_*.txt, apply_fixes.py, fix_product.py, fix_clippy.py, get_context.py, patch_oracle, patch_oracle.rs, deep_clippy.txt, rust-bug-scan.txt, ubs_out.txt, and many one-shot test_*.rs reproductions of bugs that have since been fixed (test_cow_bug.rs, test_nan_max.rs, test_polydiv*.py, test_ncx2*, test_digitize*, test_skip*, test_npz.rs, etc.).\n\nThese are NOT project state — they are agent residue. They make git status noisy, hide real changes, and risk being accidentally \"git add .\"'d by a future session. AGENTS.md Rule 1 forbids file deletion without explicit user permission, so this needs a human-in-the-loop triage pass.\n\n## Background / context for future-self\n\n- AGENTS.md Rule 1: \"YOU ARE NEVER ALLOWED TO DELETE A FILE WITHOUT EXPRESS PERMISSION.\" This is absolute. The entire triage manifest must be presented to the user for approval before any deletion occurs.\n- AGENTS.md L753: Codex agents frequently panic about \"unexpected changes\" in git status. Reducing the untracked file count directly reduces this failure mode.\n- The untracked files fall into clear categories based on naming patterns:\n  - clippy_*.txt (12+ files): clippy lint output captures — purely transient.\n  - test_*.rs (25+ files): one-off Rust reproduction files for specific bugs. Most reference bugs that have since been fixed (e.g., test_cow_bug.rs → fixed by commit ca9d3bd).\n  - test_*.py (8+ files): Python oracle reproduction scripts.\n  - fix_*.py, apply_fixes.py, get_context.py: agent automation scripts used once.\n  - test_* (no extension, 15+ files): compiled test binaries left in the repo root.\n  - patch_oracle, patch_oracle.rs: one-off oracle patching experiment.\n  - ubs_out.txt, deep_clippy.txt, rust-bug-scan.txt: tool output captures.\n\n## Goals\n\n1. **Produce a triage manifest** as a markdown file (artifacts/triage/working_tree_cleanup.md) with one row per untracked file:\n\n   | File | Category | Disposition | Rationale |\n   |------|----------|-------------|-----------|\n   | clippy_out.txt | tooling output | .gitignore | Transient lint capture |\n   | test_cow_bug.rs | fixed-bug repro | delete (pending approval) | Bug fixed in ca9d3bd |\n   | ... | ... | ... | ... |\n\n   Categories: (a) tooling-output — add to .gitignore, (b) fixed-bug-repro — safe to delete after approval, (c) useful-script — promote to scripts/dev/, (d) compiled-binary — add to .gitignore, (e) unclear — leave alone and note why.\n\n2. **Present the triage manifest to the user** for review. DO NOT delete anything until the user explicitly approves the disposition for each category.\n\n3. **After user approval, execute the approved dispositions:**\n   - .gitignore additions: append patterns to the root .gitignore.\n   - Deletions: only for files the user approved.\n   - Promotions: move to scripts/dev/ (create dir if needed).\n\n4. **Add preventive .gitignore patterns** so this doesn't recur. Proposed patterns based on observed naming:\n   ```gitignore\n   # Agent session artifacts (transient)\n   clippy_*.txt\n   deep_clippy.txt\n   rust-bug-scan.txt\n   ubs_out.txt\n\n   # Compiled test binaries in repo root\n   test_arange\n   test_contiguous\n   test_digitize\n   test_digitize_nan\n   test_div\n   test_idx\n   test_max\n   test_max_rows\n   test_min\n   test_multiple\n   test_nan_bin\n   test_nan_cast\n   test_nan_max\n   test_nan_min\n   test_nat\n   test_neg_zero\n   test_overlap\n   test_pad\n   test_parse_tab\n   test_put_along\n   test_rem_panic2\n   test_shift\n   test_shift2\n   test_solve\n   test_split\n   ```\n   Better: use a single pattern if possible. All compiled binaries in repo root have no extension and start with test_ — but we can't just ignore test_* because test_*.rs and test_*.py are also in the list. Consider a more targeted approach: ignore extensionless files matching common test binary names, or add a catch-all for files without extensions in the root.\n\n## Non-goals\n\n- Do NOT delete anything without explicit user sign-off on the triage manifest.\n- Do NOT touch artifacts/ — those modifications are intentional regeneration.\n- Do NOT move or modify files inside crates/ — those are project source code.\n- Do NOT automate this as a pre-commit hook — it's a one-time cleanup.\n\n## Verification\n\nAfter cleanup:\n1. Run `git status` and confirm the untracked file list is < 10 items (ideally 0).\n2. Run `cargo test --workspace` to verify nothing that was accidentally depended on was removed.\n3. Run `cargo check --workspace` to verify no include!() or path references broke.\n4. Verify .gitignore patterns match intended files by running `git status --ignored` and checking that the right files show up.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- [ ] Triage manifest produced with one row per untracked file.\n- [ ] User has explicitly approved the disposition of every file category.\n- [ ] Approved deletions completed.\n- [ ] .gitignore patterns added and committed.\n- [ ] Post-cleanup git status shows < 10 untracked files.\n- [ ] cargo check --workspace still passes after cleanup.\n- [ ] cargo test --workspace still passes after cleanup.\n- [ ] .gitignore patterns verified via git status --ignored.\n\n## How this serves the over-arching goals\n\nA noisy working tree directly causes the failure mode AGENTS.md L753 warns about (\"Unexpected changes (need guidance)\" — Codex panicking about files it didn't touch). Cleaning this up reduces inter-agent friction and makes git status a reliable signal again.","notes":"Manifest created at artifacts/triage/working_tree_cleanup.md. Root scratch inventory: 86 untracked regular files total, with 32 visible in git status and 54 already ignored by the existing root .gitignore. No deletions performed pending explicit user approval.","status":"in_progress","priority":3,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":60,"created_at":"2026-04-09T00:16:17.571367637Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-20T17:33:47.425868168Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["hygiene"]}
